title: For Sale:  Rare Type I Arisaka (also known as the Carcano Arisaka)
postcontent:
I never thought I'd get my hands on another one of these but, surprise, I did! This is yet another Type I Arisaka, also known as the Carcano Arisaka. This was made for the Japanese Imperial Navy by Italy so it has many Carcano features as well as Arisaka features. This one is in near new shape with a shiny bore and strong rifling.  There is one part missing, the barrel band spring, otherwise it's in near perfect condition.  There were only 60,000 of these made! The sling is original to this rifle and has writing on the back. No import marks on this one!
The sling in itself is worth quite a bit of money because of the writing on the back. I had a local professor of Modern Japanese History translate this (thank you UCA and Dr. John Schneiderwind!) and this is what he said:

"The top writing is actually katakana, which is one of Japan's phonetical alphabets. It says "Kira" 3499. That may refer to the batallion name and number the soldier was in, or something else, but I'm not familiar enough with how the imperial forces marked their various equipment to be sure. Kira is also used as both a first name (usually female) and family name. Since it's written in Katakana, I can't tell you more about the meaning of the name since Katakana, unlike Kanji, doesn't hold any intrinsic meaning in the characters. They are solely phonetic.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Original Stinger Pen Gun. Ultra RARE!
postcontent:
If you know guns, then you know how rare these are, Especially in the larger 25acp caliber.

This is an original American Derringer Mod 2 Pen Gun. These are known as the Stinger Pen Gun. this one is the larger 25acp caliber. It is all stainless Steel Construction, 2" rifled barrel and in excellent condition. It comes with the gun, hard case, cardboard box it came in and  the instruction manual.

These are NOT class 3 or tax stamp guns. in fact this is the only pen gun out there that exists that you can buy just like a handgun. title: For Trade:  Wiselite Sterling Mk.6 Carbine 9mm for CZ/Sig/PTR/FAL/VEPR/KSG/etc

postcontent:
This is a Wiselite Arms Sterling Mk.6 carbine manufactured in the late 1990s/ early 2000s. It is a semiautomatic, 16 inch barreled version of the famous British Sterling submachinegun which started production in the 1950s to replace the equally famous STEN submachinegun. In addition it is the same variety of gun used to make the E-11 blaster rifle of the Stormtroopers from Star Wars. These bad boys have been out of production for a good few years now though the manufacturer still carries replacement parts on their website and places like ApexGunParts.com also carry parts. 

This rifle has recently had its firing pin and its springs replaced and comes with 5 military 34 round Sterling SMG magazines. Surprisingly it is pretty accurate, I've nailed little ammo boxes at 110 yards with the thing. The stock is an underfolder and the rifle can be fired while the stock is folded. Take down is a breeze.

First pic isn't mine, second one is, I just suck at taking pictures...

title: For Sale:  Scam Warning
postcontent:
Beware of the M1 Garands posted today, if the deal is too good to be true, it probably is.  NEVER send money to anyone you DON'T KNOW.  ALWAYS google the seller's phone number and email.  Most of the time but not always, the seller won't give you his phone number and prefer to use emails only.  Try speaking with the seller on the phone, usually a scammer doesn't speak English well at all, but sometimes they do.  NEVER click on any links emailed to you, there are tons of ways he can cause damage to your computer and steal your personal information.   Google "types of scam" and see if the deal you working on is matching the description of a scam.
